# App Router contracts (special files)

**Replaces:** `layout-contract.mdc`, `loading-contract.mdc`, `error-boundaries.mdc`, `not-found-contract.mdc`, `template-contract.mdc`

Each file is a **runtime contract**, not a UI convenience.

| File | Meaning | Add when |
|---|---|---|
| `layout.tsx` | Authority kernel — session, tenant, shell | Every segment owning a session gate or shell |
| `loading.tsx` | Acceptable waiting state | `page.tsx` has async fetches; shell must appear instantly |
| `error.tsx` | Recoverable failure boundary | Approved durable shell boundaries only (see below) |
| `not-found.tsx` | Invalid truth boundary | Layout/page calls `notFound()` and needs shell continuity |
| `template.tsx` | Intentional remount/reset | Client Component state must reset on this exact segment change |

Component render order: `layout → template → error → [loading wraps] → not-found / page`

---

## `layout.tsx` — runtime kernel

Owns **only** what the shell needs before first render:

**Tier A (await in layout `Promise.all` — blocks shell)**
- Session gate (`requireOrgSession()` / `requireGlobalAdminSession()` / `requireRecentAuthStepUp()`)
- Tenant resolution (`organizationId`, `orgSlug`, role, permissions)
- Critical shell labels + translations
- `RouteEnvelope` construction → `RouteEnvelopeProvider`

**Tier B (Suspense + dedicated Server Component — never block)**
- Org switcher list, notifications, activity feeds, Lynx context, recent records

```tsx
// Tier A — blocks; Tier B — streams
const [adminLink, identity, t] = await Promise.all([
  canActInOrganization(org.userId, org.user.role, org.organizationId, "admin"),
  fetchOrgAdminIdentity(org.organizationId),
  getTranslations("Dashboard.nav"),
])
// Tier B example:
const controlPlane = (
  <Suspense fallback={<GlobalTopNavBarControlMenuSkeleton />}>
    <GlobalTopNavBarControlMenuSlot {...props} />
  </Suspense>
)
```

**Forbidden:** Tier B fetches in the layout `Promise.all`; domain data fetches (contacts, chunks) in `layout.tsx`; business logic.

