## `not-found.tsx` — shell-continuity 404

Renders **inside the parent layout** — shell stays mounted. Use a Client Component when recovery links need `orgSlug`:

```tsx
"use client"
import { useParams } from "next/navigation"
import { Link } from "#i18n/navigation"

export default function OrgDashboardNotFound() {
  const { orgSlug } = useParams<{ orgSlug?: string }>()
  return (
    <div className="flex min-h-[40vh] flex-col items-center justify-center gap-4 p-6 text-center">
      <p className="text-sm text-muted-foreground">404 — Page not found</p>
      {orgSlug ? <Link href={`/o/${orgSlug}/nexus`} prefetch={false}>Back to Nexus</Link> : null}
    </div>
  )
}
```

**HTTP status:** `notFound()` in a layout = true 404. `notFound()` in a page behind `loading.tsx` = 200 (streaming). For public SEO routes: call `notFound()` before any `await`/`Suspense`.

**When NOT to add:** nested segments speculatively; empty states; rare missing-record cases where the parent segment's not-found suffices.

---

## `template.tsx` — intentional remount

Use **only** when Client Component state or `useEffect` must reset on this exact segment's param change. **Defer unless the reset requirement is explicit.**

Remounts on segment param change; **does not** remount on inner-segment navigation (e.g. `dashboard/contacts → dashboard/sale` does NOT remount `dashboard/template.tsx`).

```tsx
// Transparent — adds no markup; unique key causes remount
export default function Template({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return <>{children}</>
}
```

**Never use** for visual layout, breadcrumbs, data refresh, or as a layout substitute.
